about.description: Python API client for performing REST calls to configurable data curation system (CDCS) databases
about.summary: Python API client for performing REST calls to configurable data curation system (CDCS) databases

name: cdcs
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "cdcs" %}
{% set version = "0.1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d0f5a7de7f7da6b2928b3e30962ea3fec3e8d77105742ea67336f8325590a415

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - numpy
    - pandas
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - cdcs

about:
  home: https://github.com/usnistgov/pycdcs
  license: OTHER
  license_family: OTHER
  license_file: LICENSE.TXT
  summary: 'Python API client for performing REST calls to configurable data curation system (CDCS) databases'
  description: |
    Python API client for performing REST calls to configurable data curation system (CDCS) databases
  doc_url: https://github.com/usnistgov/pycdcs
  dev_url: https://github.com/usnistgov/pycdcs

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - lmhale99
